<div id="review_3393803" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3393803" />
    <a title="Rich" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/212070-rich"><img alt="Rich" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3393803?book_show_action=true">Jul 22, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rich" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rich" href="/user/show/212070-rich">Rich</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3393803" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7269715161560734235">I would like to have given a lower rating because I simply did not enjoy the read, but there is a value to this book that I cannot deny. Powerfully written, and has great cultural insight and thought. But really, I couldn&apos;t relate very well -- perhaps that is the point in many cases. I can&apos;t explain it much better without spending more time looking at it again than I&apos;d like to, so I&apos;ll leave it at this:<br/><br/>I felt enlightened. I felt like shit. All without feeling very invested.</span>
  <span id="freeText7269715161560734235" style="display:none">I would like to have given a lower rating because I simply did not enjoy the read, but there is a value to this book that I cannot deny. Powerfully written, and has great cultural insight and thought. But really, I couldn't relate very well -- perhaps that is the point in many cases. I can't explain it much better without spending more time looking at it again than I'd like to, so I'll leave it at this:<br /><br />I felt enlightened. I felt like shit. All without feeling very invested.</span>
